        <h2>Usability Test Report</h2>
        <p>Use the UM System Usability Test Report Template as a guide when writing your test reports:</p>
        <ul><li><a href="documents/UM Usability Report Template.docx" target="_blank">UM System Usability Test Report Template</a> (.docx)</li></ul>
        <p>Note: Test report documents can be stored on a Sharepoint site or other content management platform versus compiled in a static text document.</p>
        
        <h2>Common types of testing:</h2>
        <ul>
        <li>Accessibility testing - ensuring a system is accessible for all people</li>
        <li>Compatibility testing - testing compatability with a computing environment</li>
        <li>Exception handling - testing response to exceptional or atypical input or scenarios</li>
        <li>Graphical user interface (GUI) testing - testing the interface through which users interact with electronic devices</li>
        <li>Installation testing - testing of installation/uninstallation processes</li>
        <li>Load testing - testing system under normal and anticipated peak load conditions</li>
        <li>Recovery testing - testing the recovery of a system following a system crash</li>
        <li>Regression testing - testing for errors in an existing system following an upgrade or modification</li>
        <li>Scalability testing - testing ability of system to scale up or scale out</li>
        <li>Security testing - testing ability of system to protect data and remain functional</li>
        <li>Software performance testing - testing responsiveness and stability</li>
        <li>Stress testing - testing system with load greater than operational capacity</li>
        <li>Usability testing - testing system by having it evaluated and used by users</li>
        </ul>
        
